  <mads:note type="source">Enkyk. Papyros Larous Britannika, c1996 (hdg.: Phile&#x304;tas, 330-270 B.C.;
      poet and grammarian who was part of the Greek poetical school that flourished in Alexandria in
      323 B.C. Educated by Ptolemy II and by the poet Theokritos)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Filita grammatico, 2000: p. 1 (Filita di Cos; Filita)</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Spanoudakis, K. Philitas of Cos, 2001</mads:note>
